// Step 1: User types URL in browser
// https://example.com/about.html

// Step 2: DNS Lookup
// Browser asks: "What IP address is example.com?"
// DNS responds: "93.184.216.34"

// Step 3: HTTP Request sent to server
// GET /about.html HTTP/1.1
// Host: example.com

// Step 4: Server Response
// HTTP/1.1 200 OK
// Content-Type: text/html
// [HTML file contents follow]

// Step 5: Browser parses HTML top-to-bottom
// Builds the DOM tree

// Step 6: Browser encounters linked assets
// <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">  → new HTTP request
// <img src="hero.jpg">                       → new HTTP request
// <script src="app.js" defer></script>       → new HTTP request

// Step 7: CSS applied, JS executed
// Page is fully rendered and interactive
